rComments: If you are a visual learner, do not take this class. The class is run podcast style, so most of the content is delivered by voice only. Although lectures tend to be boring, she's really helpful when it comes to test preparation. She makes and reviews a study guide before tests, and sometimes even highlights the main points in the weekly readings.
Professor Friz is one of the best instructors I have had at the university level.  Her class is very well thought out and her concern for student's understanding and progress is awesome.
